<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/6632> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #6632" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/3> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "No title preserved. Carried a law limiting amounts of single legacies to individuals (Cic. Balb. 21; Verr. 2.1.109; Gaius 2.225-226, FIRA 2.90; Ulpian 1.2, FIRA 2.262; Fr. Vat. 301, FIRA 2.531; Inst. 2.22, pr.). It must be dated before the Lex Voconia in 169 (Gaius 2.226, FIRA 2.90). See Lange 2.255, who suggests 183 B. C." .
